==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mesquit
<hw>Mes*quit"</hw> <pr>(m⟦ecr⟧s*k⟦emac⟧t")</pr> }</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Sp. <ets>mezquite</ets>; said to be a Mexican Indian word.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Aany of several small spiny trees or shrubs of
the southwestern part of North America belonging to the genus
<gen>Prosopis</gen> having small flowers in axillary cylindrical spikes
followed by large sugar-rich pods, especially the <stype>honey
mesquite</stype>, and <stype>screw-pod mesquite</stype>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Honey mesquite</b></col>. <cd>See <er>Algaroba</er>
<sd>(b)</sd>.</cd> -- <col><b>Screw-pod mesquite</b></col>, <cd>a
smaller tree (<spn>Prosopis pubescens</spn>), having spiral pods used as
fodder and sometimes as food by the Indians.</cd> -- <col><b>Mesquite
grass</b></col>, <cd>a rich native grass in Western Texas
(<spn>Bouteloua oligostachya</spn>, and other species); -- so called
from its growing in company with the mesquite tree; -- called also
<altname>muskit grass</altname>, <altname>grama
grass</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mesquite bean</ent>⟦br⟧
